Their presence and assistance in raising funds through this action undermines all claims of impartiality, which is unacceptable.
Scalia and Thomas showed little understanding of their critics, telling them that they, too, were easily combining their judicial duties with the actions of groups such as the Federalist Society.
Thomas's wife, Ginni, is a high-ranking conservative activist.
