Other features of the labor market, such as low wages, are added to unemployment and unreliability. In this administrative territory, the lowest salaries are from all over the country, according to the registers of the Mexican Social Security Institute and the Secretariat of Labor and Social Planning.
The average monthly income of workers in the state of Sinaloa was 5,352 pesetas by September, well below the national average of 7,375 pesetas.
