In addition, a total recount of votes in all ballot boxes will be possible if there is an indication that the difference between the potential winner of the election and the candidate in second place is less than or equal to one percentage point; whenever an explicit request from the party and/or coalition that nominated the candidate in second place appears at the beginning of the session.
It will also be possible to carry out a total recount if, after a proper tally, the difference between the likely winner and the candidate in second place is found to be equal to or less than one percentage point, and also whenever there is an explicit request from a political party whose candidate has finished in second place. In this case, the ballots for which partial counting has been carried out will be eliminated.
