Park or mountains?
The architects met on the occasion of the listing of the proceedings, which carries with it more than a polemic about the fees
The 16-gate municipal tender reopens the debate on the role of the Collserola Park in Barcelona.
In the mid-1980s, during the heyday of the now defunct Corporaci<0xC3><0xB3>n Metropolitana de Barcelona (CMB), this self-government printed several pamphlets in support of the Collserola Park.
The leaflet defined the mountain as a large park of metropolitan Barcelona.
What’s more, it was complemented by a numerical comparison with New York’s Central Park.
After the collapse of the CMB in 1987, the park has returned to the mind of many as the upper limit of Barcelona. The Catalan capital is one of the few that do not orient on the axis north - south, but up (mountain) - down (sea).
The qualification of Collserola as a nature park goes in this direction.
The reference was no longer Central Park, but Yellowstone with wild boars instead of the Yogi bear.
This was the position until September, when the town hall announced a mega competition consisting of 16 auditions for the same number of entrance gates to Collserola.
The gate, of course, rather records the idea of the park.
Either this, or someone is trying to place the gate on the field.
There is only one question: Collserola, park or mountain?
During the competition, both from a purely organizational point of view and on the basis of reflection on the city, this issue becomes the central theme of all Barcelona architects.
It is a subject just as crude as when two members of this old caste, chosen at a meeting in an elevator, shake hands.
And it was this act that sparked one of the rare coincidences between what the three Barcelona architects and the university professors who preceded them thought.
Miguel Roldán, Daniel Modol and Marta Bayona: the selection procedure is justified.
According to Roldán, after the issue of the Gulf Party began, "it is necessary" to discuss the "mountain side", so Ildefonso Cerd's speech on green apples was not completed.
“We have to start from the principle that the most extensive park in Barcelona is the beach.
Among other things, its high availability.
Collserola is more complex," said the architect, for whom the name "gates to Collserola" carries a "lexicological trap": we must not imagine them "as entrances to the park, but rather as delineating zones where it is possible to operate."
Modol, like Roldán and Bayona with experience in the world of urbanism, qualifies the proposal as an "intellectual challenge" presenting "some dangers".
The danger stemming from the "uncertainty that the public place project represents today" after the experience of the 1980s, which had "its swan singing" in the Forum area.
The first concern is the very definition of the boundaries where it should be built.
"To define something is to take the next step," that is, to go one step further.
"New urban planning and planning tools need to be kept in mind, because the current ones (with reference to the General Metropolitan Plan (PGM)) can cause a real disaster."
If we focus on the question in more detail, Modol believes that the Collserola valley slope can be "considered as a park", but the Barcelona part does not, for purely topographic reasons.
Modol also recalled that there is already work done by the Patronat de Collserola, which "must not end up in a landfill", although he welcomes the fact that the city hall offers his gremya that he will intervene in the project from the "first moment".
Moreover, he understands that the proximity of the mountain and the city is a kind of culvert that allows architects to engage in debate, but "doubts" that it should be this technical profile that will lead multidisciplinary teams ("it's all about skills", he adds) that need to be created: "Architects should only be tools".
Bayona suggests that the answer to the question that gave the name to this game is complex, because the global vision of Collserol is missing in the tender documents: "16 tenders have been announced that deal with all the axis of the mountain - the sea, but there is no longitudinal study that would look at the area and understand it as a whole."
This means that at least he, applied to all 16 tenders.
Otherwise, the design of one gate may refer to the concept and definition of the architect of the neighboring gate.
In his opinion, the town hall should guarantee that the zone located immediately above the Ronda de Dalt should provide equipment throughout the entire length of the zone, which would ensure a smooth transition between the city and the greenery.
